# Supabase Dev → Prod Promotion Workflow

## Key Idea

GitHub does NOT deploy database changes.

GitHub only stores:
- code
- SQL migrations (version history)

Supabase CLI is what actually applies changes to databases.

---

# Environments

| Environment | Supabase Project | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| DEV | builderlab-dev | testing changes |
| PROD | builderlab-prod | live application |

---

# 1. Create a migration

Generate a new SQL migration file:

```bash id="m1"
npx supabase migration new add_feature_x
```

Edit the generated file:

```text id="m2"
supabase/migrations/XXXXXXXX_add_feature_x.sql
```

Add your SQL changes.

---

# 2. Apply migration to DEV (first)

Link CLI to DEV:

```bash id="m3"
npx supabase link --project-ref DEV_PROJECT_ID
```

Push migrations to DEV:

```bash id="m4"
npx supabase db push
```

✔ This updates ONLY the DEV database.

---

# 3. Test in DEV

Verify:
- schema changes
- queries
- API behavior
- frontend integration

Do NOT skip this step.

---

# 4. Commit migration to GitHub

```bash id="m5"
git add supabase/migrations
git commit -m "Add feature X migration"
git push
```

✔ This only saves version history  
❌ It does NOT affect any database

---

# 5. Promote to PROD (actual deployment step)

Switch CLI to production:

```bash id="m6"
npx supabase link --project-ref PROD_PROJECT_ID
```

Apply migrations:

```bash id="m7"
npx supabase db push
```

✔ This updates the PRODUCTION database

---

# 6. Safe promotion pattern (recommended)

Always explicitly switch environments:

## DEV deploy

```bash id="m8"
npx supabase link --project-ref DEV_PROJECT_ID
npx supabase db push
```

## PROD deploy

```bash id="m9"
npx supabase link --project-ref PROD_PROJECT_ID
npx supabase db push
```

---

# What each tool actually does

## GitHub

- stores SQL migration files
- tracks history
- enables collaboration

## Supabase CLI

- reads local migrations
- applies them to selected database

## Supabase Dashboard

- manual edits (NOT recommended for schema changes)

---

# Common mistake (IMPORTANT)

❌ `git push` does NOT update database  
❌ editing Supabase dashboard does NOT sync to GitHub  
❌ PROD is NOT updated unless you run `db push` on PROD link  

---

# Recommended professional workflow

## Step 1
Create migration locally

## Step 2
Apply to DEV

## Step 3
Test thoroughly

## Step 4
Commit to GitHub

## Step 5
Manually or CI promote to PROD

---

# Advanced (recommended later)

## CI/CD automation (GitHub Actions)

- merge to `develop` → deploy to DEV
- merge to `main` → deploy to PROD

---

## Safer production strategy

- protect main branch
- require PR approval before PROD migration
- run DB backup before `db push`

---

# Summary

> GitHub stores changes  
> Supabase CLI applies changes  
> PROD is only updated when CLI targets PROD explicitly
